Arterial trunk

definition.value: Tubular organ part, the wall and lumen of which are continuous with those of the ventricles of the heart, directly or indirectly through branches of the aorta and pulmonary trunk. Examples: bronchial artery, hepatic artery, coronary artery, truncus anterior of right pulmonary artery, aorta.

label.value: Venous trunk

definition.value: Tubular organ part, the wall and lumen of which are continuous with those of the atria of the heart, directly or indirectly through tributaries of the venae cavae, pulmonary veins and the hepatic and portal veins. Examples: coronary sinus, posterior intercostal vein, hepatic vein, bronchial vein, pulmonary vein, trunk of inferior vena cava.

label.value: Lymphatic vessel

definition.value: Segment of lymphatic tree organ, the wall and lumen of which are continuous with those of the veins, directly or indirectly; together with other lymphatic vessels and lymph nodes, it constitutes the lymphatic tree organ. Examples: bronchomediastinal lymph duct, thoracic duct.
